@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

   @{b}Introduction@{ub}
  --------------

   AFind is a searching tool for Aminet. But why? Every Aminet CD has  got
   an  index  of  the  whole  Aminet.  In  this index you can search for a
   program with the help of "AminetFind", which  is  also  one  the  newer
   Aminet CDs.

   The result is a guide. Now you can click on this file and you will know
   then that you needed program is on AminetSet 1 Disk a. For someone, who
   possesses all CDs, this means, that the programm can be  on  Disk  1-7.
   Very precise!

   AFind does principally the same. But it is used a changed index,  which
   says, that the program is, for example, on Aminet 7.
@endnode
@node "Systemrequirements" "Systemrequirements"

   @{b}Systemrequirements@{ub}
  --------------------

   You need OS2. But you can handle the GUI better,  especially  by  using
   list views, if you have OS3.x.

   Of course you should have one original AminetCD or one AminetSet.

   For the index you need 2MB free memory on your  harddisk.  This  varies
   with the number of CDs.

   This is everything.
@endnode
@node "Featurelist" "Featurelist"

   @{b}Features@{ub}
  ----------

  ° Local Support.

  ° Kickstart 2.04 or higher is required.

  ° Different versions for different workbenches.

  ° Programmed according to Commodore Styleguide.

  ° Very short because of programming in assembler.

  ° On-line-Help.

  ° Length of searching process is given.

  ° Very fast because of special searching algorithm.

  ° DOS patternmatch searching is included.

  ° Only one program. (Prefs/Searcher/Inspect)

  ° Starting and installation of programs directly from AFind.

  ° Pictures are shown with adjusted viewers (GIF/JPEG/IFF).

  ° Modules are played by mouse click.

  ° UpTo, Since and Disk for specified search for old or new things or on
    only one specified CD.
@endnode
@node "Distribution" "Distribution"

   @{b}Distribution@{ub}
  --------------

   This program may be published on all public media's,  as  long  as  all
   files  aren't changed. I'd like to have a free copy, if this program is
   published on a CD.

   @{b}AFind is Shareware.@{ub} I have decided to publish a full version of  AFind,
   because  I  hope,  that everybody, who likes this program, will pay for
   it.

   I expect from every user of AFind the registration. This will  lead  me
   to include new features and to make adjustments soon.

   @{b}I'm not responsible for damages or data loss  caused  by  using  AFind.
   Usage is on your own risk!!!@{ub}
@endnode
