@node "HowToInstall" "How to install"

   @{b}How to install ?@{ub}
  ------------------

   For installation use the original Commodore  installer.  It  created  a
   directory AFind is installed to.

   @{b}Don't try to install AFind yourself!@{ub}

   If you don't have this new version of the installer, you can find it in
   my SupportBox with the magic "Installe.lha".

   Use @{"AddIndex" link "AddIndex" 0} to create an index of your Aminet-CDs.

   If you don't like AFind, you can delete the directory to destroy  AFind
   completely.
@endnode
