@node "Buglist" "Buglist"

   @{b}Buglist@{ub}
  ---------

 ° There are small problems while uncrunching  a  file.  The  routine  for
   loading  the  first  bytes of a file and then recognising the data type
   sometimes fails. Reason for this is the automatically  switch  off  and
   then  switch  on of the CD-Rom. AmigaDos creates a time-out or gets one
   from the device of the CD-ROM. So the open fails. )-8

   I hope this problem is corrected now. This error appears to me  and  my
   beta tester rarely. So I can't say that it runs 100%.

   I got attention to this problem via telephone. So  I  haven't  got  the
   name.  Please call again for writing your name into the history, if the
   error is corrected.

 ° CDRom-handler 1.8 isn't working correct when  using  AddIndex.  Install
   AmiCDFS  it  is  better, faster and 100% compatible (expect this little
   bug).
@endnode
